ks historyedit bank of new york at  wall st the bank of new york was founded on june   making it the secondoldest bank in the united states behind the bank of north america alexander hamilton wrote the new banks constitution and became the individual most actively involved in the organization of the bank of new york guiding it through its early stages the bank opened for business at the walton house in lower manhattan only a few months after the departure of british troops from american soil it opened with a capitalization of  william seton future fatherinlaw of saint elizabeth seton was named director in  to commemorate its th anniversary bny mellon created a part video series entitled looking forward  the th anniversary of the bank of new york mellon which was narrated by historian richard brookhiser and recaps the company’s history from its founding in  the segments are entitled part   new beginnings part   a company of visionaries part   a catalyst for success part   a focus on clients part   a commitment to help timelineedit  the bank of new york is founded on june   by alexander hamilton  the bank of new york was the first corporate stock to be traded on the new york stock exchange  the bank merged with the new york life insurance  trust company  the bank acquired the fifth avenue bank older bank of new york logo  the bank acquired the empire trust company  the bank formed its holding company the bank of new york company inc  bruce rappaport purchases a  stake in the bank of new york   the bank of new york acquired the irving bank corporation and moved its headquarters to one wall street now known as the bank of new york building s the bank acquired the national community banks in new jersey and the putnam trust company in connecticut  the bank of new york acquired pershing llc a provider of correspondent clearing and outsourcing services for broker dealers asset managers and financial intermediaries that same year the bank integrated lockwood financial services inc into pershing creating one of the largest providers of managed account programs with client assets totaling nearly us billion late  the bank of new york settled with federal regulators for us million regarding a money laundering scandal that began in  the illegal operation involved two russian emigres—one of whom was a vice president of the bank—moving over us billion via hundreds of wires and ended in the prosecution of at least nine individuals april   jp morgan chase  co announced they would swap their corporate trust unit for bank of new york cos retail and small business banking network the swap valued the bank of new york business at us billion and jpmorgans trust unit at us billion and gave chase access to  additional branches and  new customers in the new york new jersey and connecticut tristate area december   the bank of new york and mellon financial corporation announced a merger in which the name would be changed to the bank of new york mellon corporation or bny mellon creating the worlds largest securities servicing provider and a top asset management firm globally may  russia filed a us billion lawsuit against the bank for money laundering the suit was subsequently settled for  million merger with mellonedit madison avenue branch talks of a merger began when tom renyi approached robert kelly about a possible amalgamation between the bank of new york and mellon financial corporation the us billion deal was finalized on july   with kelly as the chief executive officer ceo of the new company and renyi as executive chairman per the deal the new board of directors is composed of ten directors appointed by the bank of new york and eight by mellon the bank of new york mellon launched its new brand identity as on october   currency trading lawsuitedit in october  the justice department and new yorks attorney general filed civil lawsuits against the bank of new york alleging foreign currency fraud the suits hold that the bank deceived pensionfund clients by manipulating the prices assigned to them for foreign currency transactions allegedly the bank selected the days lowest rates for currency sales and highest rates for purchases appropriating the difference as corporate profit the scheme is said to have generated  billion for the bank at the expense of millions of americans retirement funds and to have transpired over more than a decade purportedly the bank would offer secret pricing deals to clients who raised concerns in order to avoid discovery bank of new york has defended itself vigorously maintaining the fraud accusations are flat out wrong and warning that as the bank employs  employees in new york any damage to the bank would have negative repercussions for the state of new york see alsoedit bank of new york hoard semion mogilevich referencesedit  bank of new york mellon complete merger pittsburgh business times july     a b wolfe allis  bank of new york in kenneth t jackson the encyclopedia of new york city new haven ct  london  new york yale university press  the newyork historical society pp –   barbery hélène elizabeth seton et les commencements de leglise catholique aux etats unis  p   bnymelloncomdead link  bnymelloncomdead link  bnymelloncom dead link  bnymelloncom dead link  bnymelloncom dead link  greenhouse steven  a secret emperor of oil and shipping the new york times   quint michael  irving signs merger deal ending fight the new york times retrieved    pershing pershing llc archived from the original on september   retrieved  not in citation given  lockwood lockwood retrieved  not in citation given  russia sues bank of new york for  bln usd forbescom may   archived from the original on december   retrieved    parloff roger september   russia settles suit against us bank for a pittance cnn retrieved    a b dash eric  bank of new york and mellon will merge new york times retrieved    informationweek  magnificent seven information week retrieved  dead link  vries lloyd  bank of new york to merge 